        "properties": {
          "title": [
            [
              "since you can’t overwrite an executable file of a running program, it’s a good idea to kill running instance of the program in the installer, to avoid a failure in the middle of installation. There’s no built-in functionality to kill processes in NSIS. After spending way too much time trying to find an existing solution, I ended up writing an extension dll with necessary support command."
            ]
          ]
        },
        "type": "bulleted_list",
        "version": 1,
        "inline_content": [
          {
            "Text": "since you can’t overwrite an executable file of a running program, it’s a good idea to kill running instance of the program in the installer, to avoid a failure in the middle of installation. There’s no built-in functionality to kill processes in NSIS. After spending way too much time trying to find an existing solution, I ended up writing an extension dll with necessary support command."
